OL,6,FThe electrodes were connected to the
OL,7,Fdevice which was placed in the gap in
OL,8,Fthe skull where the bone had been
OL,9,Fremoved. The neurotransmitter was then
OL,10,Fscrewed into place.
OL,12,FOran can recharge the device daily
OL,13,Fusing wireless headphones, allowing
OL,14,Fhim to continue his hobbies.
OL,16,FSince the surgery, Oran's mum said he
OL,17,Fis much happier, "It makes the future
OL,18,Fbrighter and more attainable even. I'm
OL,19,Freally pleased that Oran gets to
OL,20,Fexperience that".
